&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nurses – Endoscopy Department&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;40 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Riverside Clinic, Brentford TW8 9HE&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary up to £35,000 p/a (Dependent on Experience)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Healthshare Limited are an independent healthcare provider. With a network of&lt;br /&gt; clinics across the country, our aim is to attract the best nursing, theatre and allied&lt;br /&gt; healthcare professionals in addition to employing outstanding non-clinical and&lt;br /&gt; support staff who underpin everything we do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Riverside Clinic is the new hospital located at Brentside Executive Park, Great West Road, Brentford.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are presently recruiting for Endoscopy Nurses. The post is based in Riverside with easy transport links to all sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be considered you must have a flexible, adaptable and an innovative approach to work and be able to proactively deliver results. Our Nurses are expect to work independently, deliver a high standard of patient-centred clinical care, possess a friendly and approachable attitude and apply outstanding team-working, communication and organisational skills to their daily practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Endoscopy experience would be beneficial however we would consider nursing candidates with no endoscopy experience. Orientation and training will be provided in order to ensure one is supported and receive sufficient training to work safely and efficiently within endoscopy environment.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Healthshare we care about your career development. Applicants will be keen learners and will actively participate in clinical teaching and in-service training sessions gaining experience, shadowing and supervision opportunities are provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Like the sound of this job? Don&#39;t miss out - apply now&lt;/p&gt;
